         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="title:2;36:32">What is Switchtec security?</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:2;39:24">Security features in Switchtec are OPTIONAL. All Switchtec devices are shipped unsecured and can be used without employing security keys. Switchtec security is made up of the following sub-features:</p>
         <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="ul:1;42:26">
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="li:1;45:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:3;48:30">Secure Boot</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="li:2;52:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:4;55:30">Secure Firmware Update </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="li:3;59:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:5;62:30">Secure RMA/debug</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:6;67:24">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="b:1;70:27">Secure Boot</b> is a mechanism to authenticate and validate firmware and configuration files within the switch. The mechanism exists to <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="i:1;72:27">extend</i> the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="i:2;74:27">Chain of Trust</i> in a system.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:7;77:24">The Chain of Trust starts with an immutable Boot ROM which is implemented in Switchtec hardware and provides a secure validation path up to the customer application. Secure boot is intended to accomplish several things: </p>
         <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="ul:2;80:26">
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="li:4;83:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:8;86:30"> Prevent persistent, otherwise undetectable, exploits which allows for a system to always return to a known trusted state even through changes in physical custody</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="li:5;90:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:9;93:30"> Prevent malicious firmware from initiating TLPs that could access or modify Endpoint data or host memory</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="li:6;97:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:10;100:31"> Authenticate customer switch configuration and firmware</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="li:7;104:29">
               <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:11;107:31"> Extend the Chain of Trust in larger system topologies from host through switch to Endpoints</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:12;112:25">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="b:2;115:27">Secure firmware update</b> is a mechanism to prevent malicious code from being loaded into the switch flash storage. This is different from secure boot. Secure boot prevents the switch from booting if an image is not properly signed. Secure firmware update ensures only properly signed images can be loaded into SPI flash. This feature also prevents denial-of-service attacks where an invalid image is loaded into SPI flash storage which results in a failure to boot. </p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:13;118:25">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="b:3;121:27">Secure RMA/debug</b> is a mechanism that allows customers to return secured devices to Microchip for debug. If a device has the highest level of security applied, debug ports such as EJTAG are also locked to prevent malicious attacks via the debug ports. Under such circumstances, a device cannot be debugged in field or by Microchip. In these cases, a secure unlock is possible by providing a challenge/response mechanism that allows Microchip to unlock a specific device for debug.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="section:2;125:33">
