         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:14;131:25">Secure Boot protects a system against threats <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="i:3;133:27">before</i> they can attack or infect it. The system (host, switch, Endpoints) will only boot with authenticated software that is trusted by the system vendor and prevents malicious software from loading during the startup process.</p>
