         <note audience="MSCCInternal" class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="note:3;254:30">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:27;257:28">Source Graphics: <xref href="http://bby1dms01.microsemi.net/DocMgmt/fileinfo.cfm?file_id=445264" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="xref:2;261:36"><?ditaot usertext?>http://bby1dms01.microsemi.net/DocMgmt/fileinfo.cfm?file_id=445264 </xref>
            </p>
         </note>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:28;266:25">Switchtec first boots with boot code which is in ROM. This code is immutable (which means it cannot be changed over time). The boot code (BL1) performs an integrity check to the flash partition map which describes the location of FW images and then validates the key manifest (which stores the keys for all other FW images) and the secondary boot loader. </p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:29;269:25">The validation of the key manifest is the root trust in the Chain of Trust, whose key is saved in onetime-programmable (OTP) device hardware. The boot ROM and on-chip fused keys serve as the hardware root of trust. Trust is extended to mutable (which means it can be changed over time) flash resident firmware after secure authentication of the BL2 image.</p>
         <fig class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="fig:2;272:28">
            <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="title:7;275:35">Secure Boot Process</title>
            <image href="graphics/trident_secure_boot_block.svg" width="6in" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="image:2;281:36"/>
         </fig>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\security\trident_security_overview.xml" xtrc="p:30;285:25">The Switchtec secure boot process is reliant on a combination of Switchtec hardware, firmware, and customer provided keys. Customer keys are burned into the device OTP memory during the securing process, details of which are covered in subsequent sections.</p>
